TELEM:Aggregator.TELEM:name: dmr
TELEM:Aggregator.TELEM:description: Diamond Rapids IMH Telemetry samples definition and transformation rules

TELC:sample.name: MAX_THREAD_ID
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Max Thread ID - highest enabled Logical Thread in the Package? Die?

TELC:sample.name: EFFICIENT_PERFORMANCE_INDICATOR
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Efficient Performance Indication (EPI) provides an approximation of the number of productive core cycles in the socket. This only provides a means to measure the relative productivity/scalability of a socket, either relative to other sockets or relative to time (past sample).

TELC:sample.name: FAN_TEMP_TARGET_OFST
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Fan Temperature Target Offset (a.k.a. T-Control) indicates the relative offset from the Thermal Monitor Trip Temperature at which fans should be engaged.

TELC:sample.name: REF_TEMP
TELC:sample.TELC:description: This field indicates the maximum junction temperature, also referred to as the Throttle Temperature, TCC Activation Temperature or Prochot Temperature. This is the temperature at which the Adaptive Thermal Monitor is activated.

TELC:sample.name: TJ_MAX_TCC_OFFSET
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Temperature offset in degrees (C) from the TJ Max. Used for throttling temperature. Will not impact temperature reading. If offset is allowed and set - the throttle will occur and reported at lower then Tj_max.

TELC:sample.name: MARGIN_TO_TJMAX
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Processor Package Temperature margin to Tjmax in S10.6 format. A negative value indicates there is margin.

TELC:sample.name: MARGIN_TO_TCONTROL
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Temperature Margin to Tcontrol in S10.6 format. Returns 0x8001 in case of error. A postive value indicates there is margin.

TELC:sample.name: FIVR_HEALTH_MONITOR
TELC:sample.TELC:description: FIVR Health Indicator Status - 2bits per FIVR

TELC:sample.name: FIVR_HEALTH_MONITOR
TELC:sample.TELC:description: FIVR Health Indicator Status - 2bits per FIVR

TELC:sample.name: FIVR_HEALTH_MONITOR
TELC:sample.TELC:description: FIVR Health Indicator Status - 2bits per FIVR

TELC:sample.name: TDC_LIMIT
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Thermal Design Current limit in units of 1 Amp. This limit is per die and not SW configurable. TDC_LIMIT == 0 indicates the feature is disabled

TELC:sample.name: TIME_WINDOW
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Length of time window over which the current limit will be used by the processor. Reported in units of 1mS. The time window is per die and not SW configurable

TELC:sample.name: CHARGE
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Total amount of charge consumed since the last reset, reported in 18.14 Coulomb. This is a monotonic increment counter with rollover

TELC:sample.name: TIME
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Time stamp when the CHARGE status was updated in units of 10ns

TELC:sample.name: POWER_LIMIT_THROTTLE_COUNTER
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Reports th accumulated throttled time the Power limiting algorithm had to clip the power limit due to hitting the lowest power state available. Units of 1mS

TELC:sample.name: FREQ_HISTOGRAM_BIN_0
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Frequency histogram bin 0 counter (Fabric in C6)

TELC:sample.name: FREQ_HISTOGRAM_BIN_1
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Frequency histogram bin 1 counter (800MHz or less)

TELC:sample.name: FREQ_HISTOGRAM_BIN_0
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Frequency histogram bin 0 counter (Fabric in C6)

TELC:sample.name: FREQ_HISTOGRAM_BIN_1
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Frequency histogram bin 1 counter (800MHz or less)

TELC:sample.name: TIME_STAMP
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Timestamp - Lower bits of the TSC when the sample was written
